    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Clean contact records with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API for Routing\n\n**Pattern:** Data Enrichment · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nClean contact records with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API for Routing. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual routing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Pull Side A (HubSpot) → Diff the Two Systems → Create Missing in MySQL → Gather Sync Results → Guard Non-Empty email → Stamp Processing Time → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to data enrichment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating routing in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: HubSpot private-app token; MySQL connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "33bbd70f-4a3c-91b9-c136-d877a10f247c",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -620
      ],
      "id": "2e4c3cc0-4314-2e2b-0694-ac7d1de2e0e4",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
